114
00:07:59,318 --> 00:08:03,538
This is why generative AI architecture
should not be discussed separately

115
00:08:03,638 --> 00:08:05,998
from data engineering and governance.

116
00:08:06,918 --> 00:08:11,498
I sometimes joke around saying that LLM
without good enterprise data is like

117
00:08:11,538 --> 00:08:17,198
hiring a brilliant intern and then locking
them in a room with outdated blinders.

118
00:08:18,198 --> 00:08:22,668
You'll still get enthusiasm, but
not always the answers you need

119
00:08:23,168 --> 00:08:24,688
That leads naturally to RAG.

120
00:08:25,288 --> 00:08:29,788
This deck makes a strong case for
why RAG is often a better enterprise

121
00:08:29,888 --> 00:08:32,108
pattern than fine-tuning alone.

122
00:08:32,688 --> 00:08:37,588
Freshness, auditability, cost
efficiency, and governance.

123
00:08:37,869 --> 00:08:41,688
Freshness matters because retrieval
lets you surface up-to-date enterprise

124
00:08:41,749 --> 00:08:46,449
knowledge without retraining every
