170
00:12:06,348 --> 00:12:12,478
" We'll fix it later," becomes a very
expensive sentence in real-time systems.

171
00:12:12,978 --> 00:12:13,887
So how do we tackle that?

172
00:12:14,448 --> 00:12:18,698
This slide lays out some key
enablers for scalable real-time AI.

173
00:12:19,617 --> 00:12:24,688
Online feature stores, streaming
pipelines, model serving infrastructure,

174
00:12:25,287 --> 00:12:31,168
and hTAP style integration between
operational and analytical systems.

175
00:12:31,668 --> 00:12:35,248
Online feature stores
support low latency lookups.

176
00:12:35,928 --> 00:12:39,068
Streaming pipelines, on the
other hand, keep features fresh.

177
00:12:40,048 --> 00:12:44,188
Model serving infrastructure gives you
auto-scaling endpoints with latency

178
00:12:44,288 --> 00:12:47,248
budget and resilience patterns.

179
00:12:47,328 --> 00:12:52,987
And hTAP integration helps AI
decisions sit inside the operational

180
00:12:53,087 --> 00:12:57,047
workflow instead of living in a
disconnected analytical corner.

181
00:12:58,007 --> 00:13:03,207
The larger point is that every
component needs to be independently

182
00:13:03,227 --> 00:13:05,547
scalable and observable.

183
00:13:05,687 --> 00:13:10,367
One slow dependency can break
the real-time contract from the

184
00:13:10,427 --> 00:13:14,107
whole experience So what should
the audience walk away with?

185
00:13:14,607 --> 00:13:20,587
First, treat data, models, and
infrastructure as version assets.

186
00:13:21,187 --> 00:13:25,487
That mindset shift is foundational
to operational maturity.

187
00:13:25,987 --> 00:13:29,687
Second, database DevOps
is not optional for AI.

188
00:13:30,187 --> 00:13:34,467
CI for data, schema governance,
and pipeline observability

189
00:13:34,628 --> 00:13:36,448
are not nice to have anymore.

190
00:13:37,227 --> 00:13:39,767
They are part of the
production foundation.

191
00:13:40,267 --> 00:13:44,127
Third, governance and observability
must be built in from the start.

192
00:13:44,687 --> 00:13:48,747
If you want AI systems that
are auditable, trustworthy, and

193
00:13:48,827 --> 00:13:52,847
sustainable in production, you cannot
retrofit those qualities later.

194
00:13:53,347 --> 00:13:55,247
Thank you for spending the time with me.

195
00:13:55,308 --> 00:13:59,947
My hope is that this session reframed
enterprise AI a little bit more, not

196
00:14:00,047 --> 00:14:05,267
just a modeling challenge and not
just LLM challenge, but as a systems

197
00:14:05,327 --> 00:14:06,427
challenge

